The Lantern Reforms' district boundary system created the administrative infrastructure within which Ashborn were classified and processed during the Ash-and-Iron years. The Reforms' "unregistered person" category — created for transient merchants who had not yet filed with the trade registry — became the intake category applied to Ashborn arriving from Cinderteeth-adjacent territories. The Reforms did not create this category with Ashborn in mind: at the time of the Reforms, Ashborn as a distinct people did not yet exist, because the Cinderteeth eruption had not yet occurred. The category was applied retroactively to a population it was never designed to accommodate, producing the misclassification that Ashborn communities have documented in their oral tradition. The lamp-line signaling system's repurposing to identify districts with unregistered persons meant that Ashborn concentrations were flagged for intake processing by the same infrastructure that guided them to the city.
